   National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration / OAR / ERL

   National Severe Storms Laboratory
       _______________________________________________________________

   [whitesquare.gif]
   The National Severe Storms Laboratory is one of NOAA's internationally
   known Environmental Research Laboratories, leading the way in
   investigations of all aspects of severe weather. Headquartered in
   Norman OK with staff in Colorado, Washington, Utah, and Wisconsin, the
   people of NSSL, in partnership with the National Weather Service, are
   dedicated to improving severe weather warnings and forecasts in order
   to save lives and reduce property damage.
   [whitesquare.gif]
       _______________________________________________________________

